* Though wounded and weakening she faught to keep the SBM active even though 
it wanted to shut down and return her to an undamaged robot mode.
If she converted now she would be weaker anyway and then in risk of being 
hurt more.
Her legs had been knocked out from under her and now she lay on the ground, 
breathing heavily but not willing to give up.
With a burst of might she heaved with every muscle she had, trying to rise 
to her feet. But Marien's sword caught her in the neck, cutting deep but the 
advancment on this mode prevented him from doing any real damage. Instead it 
annoyed her enough to swing her head at him and emit a piercing scream, at a 
frequency that could shatter glass.
But the scream was stopped short by the feeling of skin peeling again when 
Ominous and Quasar fired.
Curcuits were visible this time as the fireball from the impact disappeared, 
yellow gew oozing onto the ground. Dare anyone step in it then would be 
walking on acid.
Trying desperetly this time she heaved, her back feet gaining ground but 
sending her chin tinting into the soil before pushing with her front limbs 
and standing shakily on all fours.
Why did this have to be happening, why couldn't they all just leave them 
alone?!
Her body shook but this time with rage, jaw clenched.
Her hands dug into the ground before she heard Jackle giggle, snarling with 
absolute rage and with all that behind her she was right infront of him 
before anyone could realize that she'd move at all.
Anger, frustration all building, and Jackle was the one who it was going to 
be taken out on.
Her hands flew forward to knock him to the ground before her neck sent her 
head down towards his chest, jaws open.*

AP:* With such a quick movement, Prowl missed her completely.*
